          "date": "2014-09-24 16:36:48.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-5644 clio: yield CPU when cl_lock isn't pruned immediately",
        "message": "LU-5644 clio: yield CPU when cl_lock isn't pruned immediately\n\ncl_locks_prune() will not delete a cl_lock when its cll_holds value\nis greater than 0. In this case, the function leaves the cl_lock on\nthe object's coh_lock list and iterates in a tight loop examining\nthe same lock until all holds are released. It does not yield the\nCPU while looping. This causes CPU stalls and heartbeat faults if\nthe holds are not released quickly enough. As an example,\nosc_lock_enqueue() increments the hold count before issuing its\nLDLM_ENQUEUE request. Thus cl_locks_prune can block the CPU for the\ntime it takes to complete or timeout an RPC.\n\nThe patch allows the cl_locks_prune() task to be rescheduled if the\ncl_lock was not deleted.\n\nSigned-off-by: Ann Koehler <amk@cray.com>\nChange-Id: If64d870d813c64bf96234f63ddf3c75df5672f82\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
